---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Local Backlinks: earning quality links | visibilite-locale.online"
  description="Strategies to earn quality local backlinks and strengthen your local SEO authority."
  lang="en"
>
  <section class="border-b border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 py-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4">
      <nav class="mb-4 text-sm text-gray-500">
        <a href="/en/" class="hover:text-blue-600">Home</a> &rsaquo;
        <a href="/en/guide-seo-local" class="hover:text-blue-600">Local SEO Guide</a> &rsaquo;
        <span class="text-gray-900">Local Backlinks</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900">Local Backlinks</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Get links from websites in your region to strengthen your local authority.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-14">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 prose">
      <h2>Why local backlinks matter</h2>
      <p>
        Backlinks from local websites (city halls, associations, regional media, partners) are particularly valued by Google for local ranking. They prove your connection to the community.
      </p>

      <h2>Sources of local backlinks</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Local directories</strong>: chambers of commerce, municipal directories, professional associations</li>
        <li><strong>Local press</strong>: press releases, interviews, articles in regional media</li>
        <li><strong>Partnerships</strong>: link exchanges with complementary businesses in your area</li>
        <li><strong>Sponsorships</strong>: sponsor local events, sports clubs, or associations</li>
        <li><strong>Schools and universities</strong>: internships, guest lectures, educational partnerships</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Local link building techniques</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Create useful content for your community (local guides, market studies)</li>
        <li>Participate in local events and get mentioned on organizer websites</li>
        <li>Offer testimonials to your suppliers (they often publish them with a link)</li>
        <li>Join professional associations that list their members online</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Quality vs quantity</h2>
      <p>
        A single link from a trusted local site (regional media, institutional site) is worth more than dozens of links from low-quality directories. Always prioritize relevance and authority.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 p-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-blue-900">Related articles</p>
        <ul class="mt-2 text-blue-700">
          <li><a href="/en/blog/en-link-building-local/">Local Link Building: How to Earn Backlinks in Your Area</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
